      • checkCovTermValue

        java.util.List<? extends ProductModelSyncIssue> checkCovTermValue()
        Checks that the value of this CovTerm is available. If it is unavailable, this returns a list with a single ProductModelSyncIssue. If the value is available or is null, then an empty list is returned. (Null values for required CovTerms should be caught by validation.)
        Returns:
        null if CovTerm is available or null, a List with a single issue otherwise
